embeds.title: Command Usage
embeds.description: You can find the message ID a role is on with **@Zira list**.

fields.name: @Zira delete check <message ID>
fields.value: Checks for deleted roles on a message.

fields.name: @Zira delete all <message ID>
fields.value: Remove all roles from a message.

fields.name: @Zira delete <message ID> <role>
fields.value: Remove a role from a message

fields.name: @Zira autorole user <role>
fields.value: Give roles for when a person joins

fields.name: @Zira autorole bot <role>
fields.value: Give roles for when a bot joins

footer.text: If you would like to remove a role that is setup with autoroles, just do the command you used to set it up again.

fields.name: @Zira embed [Embed JSON]
fields.value: Create an embed that will be used as the active message.

fields.name: @Zira delete
fields.value: Delete a role that has been setup.

fields.name: @Zira edit <message ID> <new message>
fields.value: Edit a message sent by Zira.

fields.name: @Zira autorole
fields.value: Give roles to be given when a member joins

fields.name: @Zira dm
fields.value: Send the user a DM whenever they react to get or remove roles
